

An analysis large losses at the roulette table which occurred
on March 10, 12 and 15 yield the following results.

Finding: 
Player: Mylie Schmidt and Dealer: Billy Jones are
always and uniquely associated with the 13 large losses.
The data suggests they are working together.

Reasons:
* Large losses occurred 13 times on those days.
* In all 13 instances, Mylie Schmidt was playing.
* No other player was present during more than one of the large losses.
* In all 13 instances, Billy Jones was dealing.
* No other dealer was present during more than one of the large losses.

